@startuml 2B_Upload_Manage_Assets
title 2-B · Upload & Manage Media Assets (UC-T05, UC-T16, UC-T17)

start
|Tenant Admin (Owner/Admin)|
:Open media or profile asset manager;
:Select asset target\n(profile image / media gallery / discography / merch image);
:Choose file from device;

|System|
:Verify tenant status = ACTIVE;
:Check plan entitlement and storage quota;
:Validate file size, extension and MIME type;
if (Validation passed?) then (No)
  :Return 422 or 403 with clear error;
  stop
else (Yes)
  :Upload file to object storage;
  :Create media asset metadata record\nwith tenant scope;
endif

if (Asset target?) then (Profile Image)
  :Link asset to IdolProfile;
elseif (Asset target?) then (Media Gallery)
  |Tenant Admin (Owner/Admin)|
  :Enter title, description and visibility;
  |System|
  :Create or update MediaGallery item;
elseif (Asset target?) then (Discography)
  |Tenant Admin (Owner/Admin)|
  :Enter release title, type, date and platform links;
  |System|
  :Create or update Discography record;
else (Merch Image)
  :Attach asset to MerchProduct or variant;
endif

|System|
:Invalidate fansite cache;
:Updated asset becomes available according to visibility;

|Tenant Admin (Owner/Admin)|
if (Replace or remove old asset?) then (Yes)
  |System|
  :Mark old asset inactive or detach it\nwithout breaking historical records;
else (No)
  :Keep current asset;
endif

stop
@enduml
